"box-sizing: content-box; padding: 15px 0px 15px 24px; height: 240px;"><div class="ds-virtual-list-visible-items" style="position: relative; transform: translateY(0px); --ds-virtual-list-transform-y: 0px; --ds-virtual-list-ios-compensation-y: 0px;"><div class="_81e7b5e"><div class="_72b6158">i want I checked your GitHub 👉
([Open your profile](https://docs.github.com/en/account-and-profile/setting-up-and-managing-your-github-profile/customizing-your-profile/setting-your-profile-to-private?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

Now let’s turn it into something that looks **🔥 professional, clean, and impressive to teachers or recruiters**.

---

# 🚀 1. First — Your Profile MUST Have a “Wow” README

This is the #1 thing that makes profiles look **pro**.

👉 Create a repository with **exactly your username**
Example: `bamites1-sketch/bamites1-sketch`

Then add a `README.md`.

### 💡 Use this template (simple but powerful)

```md
&lt;h1 align="center"&gt;Hi 👋, I'm Ambi&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3 align="center"&gt;💻 Aspiring Backend Developer | Django Lover&lt;/h3&gt;

---

🌱 I’m currently learning:
- Django
- Backend Development
- Database Design

💡 I’m interested in:
- Building real-world web apps
- Clean UI/UX systems
- Automation tools

🚀 My Projects:
- 📇 Contact Directory System
- 🎓 E-learning Platform
- 🛠 More coming soon...

📫 How to reach me:
- Email: your@email.com

---

### 🔥 Skills
- Python 🐍
- Django ⚡
- HTML, CSS 🎨
- Git &amp; GitHub 🔧

---

### 📊 GitHub Stats
![Stats](https://github-readme-stats.vercel.app/api?username=bamites1-sketch&amp;show_icons=true&amp;theme=tokyonight)

![Top Languages](https://github-readme-stats.vercel.app/api/top-langs/?username=bamites1-sketch&amp;layout=compact&amp;theme=tokyonight)
```

---

# 🎨 2. Make It Look Premium (This is what impresses teachers)

### Add:

* ✅ Emojis (not too many, but clean)
* ✅ Centered titles
* ✅ Sections with lines (`---`)
* ✅ Badges (very professional)

Example badges:

```md
![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3776AB?style=for-the-badge&amp;logo=python&amp;logoColor=white)
![Django](https://img.shields.io/badge/Django-092E20?style=for-the-badge&amp;logo=django&amp;logoColor=white)
```

---

# 🧠 3. Fix Your Repositories (VERY IMPORTANT)

Right now, most students forget this part 👇

### Every repo should have:

* ✅ Good name (not `project1`)
* ✅ Description
* ✅ README with:

  * What it does
  * Features
  * Screenshot (🔥 very powerful)
  * How to run it

### Example structure:

```md
# 📇 Contact Directory System

A Django web app to manage contacts.

## ✨ Features
- Add, edit, delete contacts
- Profile picture upload
- Search system
- Grouping contacts

## 🛠 Tech
- Django
- SQLite
- HTML/CSS

## 📸 Screenshot
(add image here)

## ▶️ Run
pip install -r requirements.txt  
python manage.py runserver
```

---

# 🧩 4. Pin Your BEST Projects

On your profile:
👉 Click **Customize profile → Pin repositories**

Choose:

* Your contact system
* Your e-learning project
* Any clean project

💡 Only 3–6 projects → keep it clean!

---

# 🔥 5. Make It Look “Active”

Even if you're still learning:

* Commit regularly
* Small updates daily
* Push improvements

This builds your **green contribution graph** 📈
(which recruiters LOVE)

---

# 🧼 6. Clean Professional Touches

* ❌ Remove messy repos
* ❌ Remove test/empty repos
* ✅ Use clear names:

  * `django-contact-app`
  * `e-learning-platform`
  * `portfolio-website`

---

# 🎯 7. Next-Level (if you want to stand out HARD)

Add:

* 🔥 Demo video (record your app)
* 🌐 Live link (if hosted)
* 📸 UI screenshots
* 🎨 Beautiful UI (you already like this)

---

# 💬 Honest Advice (important)

Your profile doesn’t need to be “perfect”
👉 It needs to show:

* You **build things**
* You **improve**
* You **understand basics well**

That alone already puts you ahead of MANY students.

